d 'NAICS_TO_FF': module to convert NAICS codes to Fama-French industry classifications
d
d	 baics_to_ff converts NAICS codes to Fama-French   
d industry classifications. The command supports all major
d Fama-French industry	  classification schemes: FF5, FF10, FF12,
d FF17, FF30, FF38, FF48, and FF49.    The command accepts both
d numeric and string NAICS codes. String NAICS codes are   
d automatically converted to numeric values. Non-numeric strings
d (e.g., "XXXX") are	treated as missing.    The Fama-French
d industry classifications are widely used in empirical accounting
d and	 finance research to group firms by industry. These
d classifications are based on	  four-digit SIC codes and are
d maintained by Kenneth R. French on his data library	 website. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: NAICS codes
d KW: SIC codes
d KW: Fama
d KW: French
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 and sic_to_ff from SSC (q.v.)
d
d Distribution-Date: 20251221
d
d Author: Kelvin Law,   Nanyang Technological University
d Support: email klaw@@ntu.edu.sg
d
f naics_to_ff.ado
f naics_to_ff.sthlp
